The New York Stock Exchange said it
is reviewing trades that sent shares of  Anadarko Petroleum Corp. (APC) 
down as much as 99 percent to 1 cent in a series of transactions
in the final second of trading.  The stock recovered and ended the session at $90.03, up 2.5
percent on the day.  The  26 trades  occurred on the NYSE where the shares are
listed, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Rich Adamonis ,
a spokesman for NYSE Euronext, didnâ€™t immediately respond to a
